We are thrilled to announce that our school has achieved outstanding results in the 2023 Kenya Certificate of Secondary Education (KCSE) examinations. With a mean score of 85%, we have set a new school record and ranked among the top 10 schools nationally.

**Key Highlights:**
- 92% of students attained university entry grades (C+ and above)
- 15 students achieved straight A grades
- 45% of students scored A- and above in Mathematics and Sciences
- 100% transition to university for all eligible candidates

These exceptional results reflect the dedication of our teaching staff, the hard work of our students, and the unwavering support from parents and guardians. Our STEM program, introduced three years ago, has shown remarkable success with students excelling in Physics, Chemistry, and Biology.

The Principal, Dr. Elizabeth Muthoni, commended the students and staff: "This achievement is a testament to our holistic approach to education, combining academic excellence with character development. We are proud to nurture not just academically gifted students, but well-rounded individuals ready to contribute to society."

Celebrations will be held on Friday, 15th March 2024, at the school auditorium. All parents, alumni, and well-wishers are invited to join us in celebrating this remarkable achievement.
